Textual_Unit: air intan ad citaacæ rebeca inní isác · doarblaing den chamull forambói · aromalldoit spirto · síc dano doarblaing indeclais dinchamull indiumsa 7 innandrochgní[mae] forsarobae intan adcondairc sponsum .i. christum
Translation: For when Rebecca first saw that Isaac, she sprang from the camel on which she was, for humility of spirit. Thus, then, the Church has sprung from the camel of pride and of evil deeds on which she had been, when she has beheld the groom, namely, Christ.

Textual_Unit: .i. inchethardataid .i. arnap samlid beith ær creitemni condib sain persan maic de 7 maic duini linn .i. condib cretem cet[h]eora persann linn .i. persan athar 7 maicc de 7 maicc duini . 7 spiurto noib . .
Translation: That is, the quaternity (set of four), namely, that our belief should not be thus, that we should deem different the person of the Son of God and (that) of the Son of Man; that is, so that it should be a belief in four persons with us, namely, the person of the Father, and (the person) of the Son of God and (the person) of the Son of Man, and (the person) of the Holy Spirit.

Textual_Unit: .i. ba bés leusom dobertis daboc leu dochum tempuil 7 noleicthe indalanái fon díthrub co pecad in popuil 7 dobertis maldachta foir 7 no[o]ircthe didiu [an]d op[opul] tarcenn ap[ecthae] indaile
